From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Alexandre Derumier <aderumier@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 13:34:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] rpcs3: namco arcade support (lightgun, USIO JVS I/O, USBMEM LDD)

Combined patch on top of RPCS3 v0.0.41:
- evdev lightgun input handler: absolute devices (guns, mice) report
  screen coordinates directly; relative mice (REL_X/Y) and touchpads are
  integrated into a centred virtual pointer.
- USIO arcade JVS I/O: separate System 357 lightgun path
  (translate_input_gun) from the Tekken/Taiko layouts; Tekken 6/BR JVS
  layout (m_is_tekken6); Razing Storm gun response, expansion-mode and
  hopper handling; lightgun aim via JVS analog; full gun button map; and
  the Dead Storm steering wheel as an incremental rotary encoder.
- query the registered USBMEM LDD so sys_fs_stat reports the USB drive as
  unmounted while the PS3A-USBMEM dongle driver is loaded (fixes Tekken 6 /
  T6BR USB KEY ERROR); also forces the lower USIO product version for Tekken 6.
- debounced auto-save of the USIO SRAM (calibration/settings) shortly after
  the game writes it, since Batocera exits skip the device destructor.
---
